Q-6:
Answer:

	Data size:
	One integer = 4 bytes.
	One long long = 8 bytes.
	One character = 1 byte

	There are 100 integer elements in a array
	If 1 integer take 4 byte then 	100 integer data size:400 bytes.

	Again there are 100 long long integer elements in a array
	If 1 long long integer take 8 byte then 100 long long integer data size:800 bytes.


	Again there are 100 character elements in a array.
	If 1 character take 8 byte then 100 character data size:100 bytes.
